description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshcore/adapter.c
Lines: 266-276

The pending_head and pending_tail functions access the pending array without bounds checking:
```c
static struct lichen_meshcore_pending_event *
pending_tail(struct lichen_meshcore_adapter *adapter)
{
    return &adapter->pending[adapter->pending_tail];
}

static const struct lichen_meshcore_pending_event *
pending_head(const struct lichen_meshcore_adapter *adapter)
{
    return &adapter->pending[adapter->pending_head];
}
```

While pending_head and pending_tail are kept in bounds by the modulo operations in pending_push/pending_pop, there is no defensive check here. If pending_head or pending_tail were ever corrupted (memory corruption, uninitialized use), this would cause out-of-bounds access.

The BUILD_ASSERT at line 47-48 ensures indices fit in uint8_t, but doesn't prevent values >= ARRAY_SIZE(adapter->pending).

Consider adding assert(adapter->pending_head < ARRAY_SIZE(adapter->pending)) for defensive programming.
